  "prompt": "How do I thank my teachers?",
  "response": "Here are some thoughtful ways to thank your teachers:\n\n1. Written methods\n- Write a heartfelt thank you card\n- Send a sincere email expressing gratitude\n- Write a letter detailing specific ways they've helped you\n- Create a handmade thank you note\n\n2. Verbal approaches\n- Tell them in person how much you appreciate them\n- Share specific examples of how they've inspired or helped you\n- Compliment them sincerely during or after class\n\n3. Small gestures\n- Give a small, thoughtful gift\n- Bring them a small treat or coffee\n- Offer to help them with classroom tasks\n- Recommend them to other students\n\n4. Long-term appreciation\n- Stay in touch after graduation\n- Update them on your progress\n- Share how their teaching influenced your life\n\n5. Formal recognition\n- Nominate them for teaching awards\n- Write positive recommendation letters\n- Provide positive feedback to school administration\n\nTips:\n- Be genuine and specific\n- Be respectful\n- Choose an approach that matches your relationship with the teacher\n- Consider your school's guidelines about gifts\n\nRemember, teachers often appreciate sincere recognition more than expensive gifts.",
